kid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}, {\"begin\": 359, \"end\": 364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997364739, \"rank\": 2.636125944729398e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simbine, who was in the top five but missed out on a medal at the last two editions of the Olympics, won his heat in 10.03 seconds, booking his place in the semifinals to be held on Sunday night.\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\udd25 Akani Simbine Qualifies in Heat 6!\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\udd25Time: 10:03#TeamSA#ForMyCountry#Olympics2024pic.twitter.com/Rvplj5SCei  \\\"I am happy to be here and it's the first time on this track for me and I am looking forward to tomorrow,\\\" Simbine said after his race.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was set to be joined in the penultimate round by Shaun Maswanganyi, who finished third in his heat in 10.06, and Benjamin Richardson, who was fourth in his heat in 10.06.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"score\": 0.9999968692872139, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Maswanganyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\"}, {\"begin\": 929, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.888563169374832, \"rank\": 0.12280199798077734, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9986682881541933, \"rank\": 0.0013333255107332042, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later on day eight of theParis Games, Tshepo Tshite finished fourth in his heat in the men's 1 500m repechage round in 3:35.35, missing out on a spot in the final by 0.03, while countryman Ryan Mphahlele was 11th in his repechage race in 3:36.64.\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tshepo_Tshite\", \"score\": 0.9999999939166173, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tshepo Tshite\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tshepo_Tshite\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tshepo_Tshite\"}, {\"begin\": 1177, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.981412247432948, \"rank\": 0.009837460779412966, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, in other events, the SA women's hockey team lost 1-0 to the United States in their last pool match, ending their Olympic campaign without a win.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1307, \"end\": 1320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.586036122187308, \"rank\": 0.6653108320484468, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Road cyclist Ryan Gibbons ended 69th in the men's race, nearly 20 minutes off the pace.\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1398, \"end\": 1405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_cycling\", \"score\": 0.9212298792193915, \"rank\": 0.08521903089254751, \"text\": \"cyclist\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Gibbons_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9846123071128813, \"rank\": 0.015625000000001603, \"text\": \"Ryan Gibbons\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Gibbons_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Gibbons_(cyclist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Single sculls rower Paige Badenhorst finished second in the women's C final in 7:27.76, after missing out on the medal battle which was contested in the A final.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowing_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999969643341, \"rank\": 3.0357028710219377e-09, \"text\": \"rower\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowing_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowing_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1502, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Satchel_Paige\", \"score\": 0.5390104291974187, \"rank\": 0.6641960862246293, \"text\": \"Paige\",